-- Eletrobras to Build High-Voltage Power Network in Mozambique, RM Reports
-- Fred Katerere
-- 2010-06-18T07:35:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-18/eletrobras-to-build-high-voltage-power-network-in-mozambique-rm-reports.html

          
          
             Centrais Eletricas Brasileiras SA 
agreed to build a 1,400 kilometer (870 mile) high-voltage power
network linking  Mozambique â€™s Cahora Bassa hydropower dam to the
capital, Maputo,  Radio Mozambique  reported.  
 The project will cost $2.8 billion and will be preceded by
a feasibility study that is expected to be completed by early
2011, the Maputo-based broadcaster said, without citing anyone.  
